cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the task of single image super resolution, which is a well-established problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel module that can wrap any existing SR network, which can be seen as a contribution to machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions use cases in medical imaging and graphics, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.GR (Graphics) are also possible sub-categories.
